    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so you're saying the environment could actually be seen as an aggravating factor? that sounds a bit counter-intuitive. wouldn't the systemic disadvantage be a mitigating factor instead, like an excuse for why they might have been in that situation? why would a court treat his background as something that makes the crime worse?",
